The defendant James D Vinson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CRT:  We did SEHR yesterday - Atty Waterman has question

Def is serving another sentence in 16CF54, w/ release date of 5-29-16.  I spoke w/ def's cousin, who left for AL this week & is no longer in WI - he said he could not come back & get def
CRT:  OK - so we need to clarify - def is here until 29th of May on sentence in 16CF54 - we can release him on 29th of May on this sentence also & he will then have 60 days after that date to establish residency in AL & if he does, the sentence will be Vacated - if he does not establish residency in AL w/in 60 days from 5-29-16, def will need to return to LCJ to serve out balance of sentence - CRT warns def, if he doesn't come back he will be Guilty of another Felony
